This paper is about improving end-to-end automatic speech recognition (ASR) systems by addressing the issue of speaker mismatch. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which covers topics related to natural language processing, including speech recognition. The paper also proposes a new model architecture that incorporates a speaker attention module, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning and neural networks, making cs.SD (Sound) another likely category. Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed model on a speech recognition task, which falls under cs.LG (Learning). The paper also involves techniques such as attention mechanisms and embeddings, which are commonly used in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) research.
